There are two Option to get the access key from Azure Storage:
 
If it can be add to secure environment variable - We can read from System environment variable.
2. a) We need to write the code to get the key from Azure Storage Pipeline.
    b) We would required below details:
         Set your Azure credentials
         tenantId = "your-tenant-id";
         clientId = "your-client-id";
         clientSecret = "your-client-secret";
         subscriptionId = "your-subscription-id";
         resourceGroupName = "your-resource-group-name";
         storageAccountName = "your-storage-account-name";
     c) Below Dependency we would required: (FYI - This is not available in nexus)
<dependency>
<groupId>com.azure</groupId>
<artifactId>azure-resourcemanager</artifactId>
<version>2.21.0</version> <!-- Make sure you are using the latest version -->
</dependency>
